Ubuntu / Debian quick installation:
####################
- Download install-Elvex.sh
- Exec the script: . ./install-Elvex.sh
That it !

autotool installation:
####################
aclocal
automake −a
autoconf
./configure
make
make clean
sudo make install

cmake compilation
####################
cmake .
make
// make elvex/buildLexicon/postedition links on /usr/local/bin (or configure CMakeLists.txt)

Once you have installed Elvex execute these commands:
####################

. ./try-me.sh

The full compilation of Elvex requires the following tools on your computer:
— g++
— flex (only if you need to recompile lex files)
— bison (only if you need to recompile yacc file)
— aclocal
— automake 
— autoconf
— libxml2-dev
- cmake
